"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DBSCAN `fit` method expects the input `X` to be either a feature array of shape (n_samples, n_features) or a distance matrix of shape (n_samples, n_samples) if `metric='precomputed'`. In the provided code, `get_point_distance` is used as a custom metric, but the input to `fit` is a feature array, not a distance matrix. This is incorrect usage.\",\n  \"patch\": \"35c35,36\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(\\n---\\n> distances = euclidean_distances(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric='precomputed').fit(distances)\\n\"\n}"